<ChannelTradeLayout
  title="AI Facebook Messenger for Plumbing Contractors | Rapid Receptionist"
  description={`AI Facebook Messenger for UK plumbing contractors. Converts bathroom renovation photos into refit enquiries and builder connection bookings. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/plumbing-contractors/ai-facebook-messenger/"
  channelName="AI Facebook Messenger"
  tradeName="Plumbing Contractor"
  tradeNamePlural="Plumbing Contractors"
  tradeSlug="plumbing-contractors"
  headline="AI Facebook Messenger for Plumbing Contractor Companies"
  accentWord="Plumbing"
  subhead="You post four photos of a complete bathroom renovation in a Victorian terrace in Jericho. Photo one: the before — a cramped bathroom with a plastic bath panel, a pedestal basin blocking the doorway, a close-coupled WC with a stained cistern, and a gravity shower over the bath barely producing a stream. Photo two: the strip-out — bare plaster removed behind the bath revealing corroded copper pipework and a crumbling cast-iron soil connection. Photo three: the rough-in — new 15mm copper supplies soldered to a Megaflo Eco 210i unvented cylinder in the airing cupboard, a new 110mm PVC soil connection boss-strapped to the existing stack, and PEX underfloor heating loops laid on insulation across the concrete floor. Photo four: the complete bathroom — a walk-in shower with frameless glass screen and Hansgrohe iBox thermostatic valve, wall-hung Villeroy & Boch Subway 2.0 WC with in-wall Geberit Sigma cistern, a wall-mounted vanity basin with a chrome monobloc mixer, underfloor heating beneath large-format porcelain tiles. One hundred and twelve likes, twenty-seven shares. A homeowner in Summertown messages: 'Our bathroom looks exactly like your before — 1930s terrace, same plastic panel, same terrible shower. Want everything the same as your after — walk-in shower, wall-hung WC, vanity basin, underfloor heating. About the same room size. We would also need the old pipework replaced. Can you come and survey? Available most evenings.' You are in an airing cupboard commissioning a cylinder. Without AI Messenger, the message waits. With it, the AI asks about the existing hot water system and whether the mains pressure is adequate for an unvented cylinder. She confirms a gravity system and good mains. Wednesday you call: Summertown 1930s terrace, full strip-and-refit, walk-in shower Hansgrohe, wall-hung WC Geberit, vanity, UFH, old pipe replacement, gravity to unvented upgrade, evening survey."
  scenario="It is 11pm on a Friday. A facilities manager for a prep school in North Oxford messages about a summer holiday washroom project: 'Evening — head teacher wants the boys' and girls' washrooms fully refitted during the six-week summer holiday. Each washroom has four WCs, three basins, and an accessible cubicle. Current sanitaryware is 1990s and failing. Need modern Armitage Shanks sanitaryware, sensor taps, TMV2 on every basin, new waste runs, and redecoration. Total of two washrooms. Can you do the plumbing in weeks one and two so the decorator follows? Building Regs Part G and safeguarding-compliant specification required. Budget approved.' Without AI Messenger, the school project waits until Monday. With AI Messenger, the reply at 11:01pm: 'Thank you — a six-week summer holiday programme for two washrooms is a typical school refurbishment timeline. Could you confirm the existing pipework material and whether the hot water source is a centralised boiler or individual water heaters?' He confirms copper and centralised boiler. Saturday you review: North Oxford prep school, 2 washrooms, 4 WCs + 3 basins + accessible each, Armitage Shanks, sensor taps, TMV2, Part G, weeks 1-2, decorator follows, centralised boiler, budget approved."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-facebook-messenger/"
  tradePageUrl="/plumbing-contractors/ai-receptionist/"
  ctaHeadline="Turn 112 Likes on a Jericho Bathroom into a Summertown Strip-and-Refit"
  ctaSubhead={`Four photos of a Victorian terrace reborn — Hansgrohe, Geberit, Villeroy & Boch, and underfloor heating — earn a hundred and twelve likes. AI Messenger converts the neighbour's message into a full renovation survey. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
